#########################
### Used ROOT Classes ###
#########################

Used:
<TCanvas.h>           basic canvas class
<TStyle.h>            style class
<TLegend.h>           draw legend class
<TH1.h>               1D histogram class

Not used:
<TF1.h>               draw 1D functions class
<TH2.h>               2D histogram class
<TGraph.h>            graphics class
<TNtuple.h>           N-tuple class
<TVector3.h>          three-vector class
<TLorentzVector.h>    Lorentz vector class
<TRandom.h>           random number generation class
<TRandom3.h>          extended random number generation class
<TROOT.h>             entry point to the ROOT system
<TChain.h>            access to collection of files containg TTree objects
<TFile.h>             a ROOT file is a suite of consecutive data records (TKey's)
<TTree.h>             a TTree object consists of a list of independent branches (TBranch)
<TPaveText.h>         a PaveText is a Pave (see TPave) with text, lines or/and boxes inside.
<Rtypes.h>            basic types used by ROOT


